{"word":"G1210 - δέω - déō - deh'-o - Bind","slug":"G1210","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">δέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>déō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>deh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bind"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B4;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9; - deo&#x0304;</b> - <i>deh'-o</i><p/>A primary verb; to <i>bind</i> (in various applications, literally or figuratively): - bind, be in bonds, knit, tie, wind. See also <a href=\"#/G1163\">G1163</a>, <a href=\"#/G1189\">G1189</a>."}]}